# UI Test Account Pool
#
# Used by gitlab_issue_campaign_dispatcher to allocate distinct test accounts
# per concurrent subagent. Each subagent receives accounts_per_issue accounts
# (one per robot test file, default 10). The system under test logs out an
# account when the same credentials log in twice, so concurrent subagents
# AND concurrent robot executions MUST use different accounts.
#
# With max_concurrent_subagents=N and accounts_per_issue=K, this pool MUST
# contain at least N*K entries — otherwise the dispatcher aborts the tick
# (No-Fallback Policy: never share an account between two in-flight runs).
#
# Format: one account per line, "username:password". Lines starting with #
# and blank lines are ignored. Trailing whitespace is trimmed.
#
# Edited at deployment time, like gitlab.env. Trigger inputs do not override
# this file. Read by scripts/load_ui_accounts.sh.

F100001:123456
